## Step 8 - Create the Application Secret Manually

Use real production values. Do not commit these values to Git.

Example:

```bash
kubectl create secret generic pharma-erp-app-secrets \
  -n pharma-erp \
  --from-literal=JWT_SECRET=replace-with-256-bit-secret \
  --from-literal=AUTH_MONGODB_URI="mongodb+srv://username:password@cluster.mongodb.net/pharma_auth_db?retryWrites=true&w=majority&appName=PharmaERP" \
  --from-literal=EMPLOYEE_MONGODB_URI="mongodb+srv://username:password@cluster.mongodb.net/pharma_employee_db?retryWrites=true&w=majority&appName=PharmaERP" \
  --from-literal=CATALOG_MONGODB_URI="mongodb+srv://username:password@cluster.mongodb.net/pharma_catalog_db?retryWrites=true&w=majority&appName=PharmaERP" \
  --from-literal=INVENTORY_MONGODB_URI="mongodb+srv://username:password@cluster.mongodb.net/pharma_inventory_db?retryWrites=true&w=majority&appName=PharmaERP" \
  --from-literal=PROCUREMENT_MONGODB_URI="mongodb+srv://username:password@cluster.mongodb.net/pharma_procurement_db?retryWrites=true&w=majority&appName=PharmaERP" \
  --from-literal=SALES_MONGODB_URI="mongodb+srv://username:password@cluster.mongodb.net/pharma_sales_db?retryWrites=true&w=majority&appName=PharmaERP" \
  --from-literal=PRODUCTION_MONGODB_URI="mongodb+srv://username:password@cluster.mongodb.net/pharma_production_db?retryWrites=true&w=majority&appName=PharmaERP" \
  --from-literal=QUALITY_MONGODB_URI="mongodb+srv://username:password@cluster.mongodb.net/pharma_quality_db?retryWrites=true&w=majority&appName=PharmaERP" \
  --from-literal=WAREHOUSE_MONGODB_URI="mongodb+srv://username:password@cluster.mongodb.net/pharma_warehouse_db?retryWrites=true&w=majority&appName=PharmaERP" \
