## Step 10 - Update Each Deployment Manifest Manually

Your DevOps repository should contain one Deployment and one Service manifest for each workload.

Each backend Deployment should contain these values:

| Field | Required Value |
| --- | --- |
| `metadata.namespace` | `pharma-erp` |
| container image | your ECR image for that service |
| container port | service port from the table above |
| readiness probe path | `/api/v1/actuator/health` |
| liveness probe path | `/api/v1/actuator/health` |
| env from Secret | `pharma-erp-app-secrets` |
| env from ConfigMap | `pharma-erp-service-config` |

Each frontend Deployment should contain these values:

| Field | Required Value |
| --- | --- |
| `metadata.namespace` | `pharma-erp` |
| container image | `pharma-erp-frontend` image from ECR |
| container port | `80` |
| readiness probe path | `/` |
| liveness probe path | `/` |

Each Service manifest should use these ports:

| Service | Service Port | Target Port |
| --- | --- | --- |
| `auth-service` | `8081` | `8081` |
| `employee-service` | `8082` | `8082` |
| `medicine-catalog-service` | `8083` | `8083` |
| `inventory-service` | `8084` | `8084` |
| `procurement-service` | `8085` | `8085` |
| `sales-distribution-service` | `8086` | `8086` |
