## Recommended Production Notes

- Use MongoDB Atlas or another managed MongoDB service instead of running MongoDB inside the cluster for production.
- Store secrets in AWS Secrets Manager, External Secrets Operator, or Sealed Secrets if your platform supports it.
- Keep Kubernetes manifests in a separate infra or GitOps repository.
- Promote images with immutable tags such as `v1.0.0`, `v1.0.1`, `v1.1.0`.
- Avoid using `latest` in any environment beyond local testing.
